      "writtenOn": "2017-05-08T21:40:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "No, uint32 was produced by the go tool, that part is unchanged. \nThe go tool does not fill in the Go types correctly when enums are used in structs. \ni.e. you get \n\n\ntype ImageInfo struct {\n\tWidth\t\tint32\n\tHeight\t\tint32\n\tColorType\tuint32\n\tAlphaType\tuint32\n}\n\ninstead of \n\t\ntype ImageInfo struct {\n\tWidth     int32\n\tHeight    int32\n\tColorType ColorType\n\tAlphaType AlphaType\n}\n\nWhich undermines type safety in Go.",
      "parentUuid": "bfd5780e_e38689b8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 8,
        "startChar": 26,
        "endLine": 8,
        "endChar": 69
